      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, you are correct. To populate the PCIeFunctionCollection, you need to establish an association between the PCIeDevice object path and the Function* paths.\n\nIn my implementation, for example, the Function0 has an association pointing back to the device:\n```\n$ busctl get-property xyz.openbmc_project.GpuSensor \\\n  /xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/GPU_0_0/Function0 \\\n  xyz.openbmc_project.Association.Definitions Associations\n\na(sss) 1 \"exposed_by\" \"exposing\" \"/xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/GPU_0_0\"\n```\nYou should add an association (exposed_by/exposing) under your Function* paths to link them to the S0B0D0 parent device path. This will allow bmcweb to correctly discover and list the members in the collection",
      "parentUuid": "ec847ba1_9dcf909b",
      "revId": "0e0a7be93409bce80484e845cfec42276f19ade5",
